{"parse":{"title":"Menachem Banitt","pageid":39828570,"revid":822315448,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:252px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Menachem_1970.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f6/Menachem_1970.jpg/250px-Menachem_1970.jpg\" width=\"250\" height=\"329\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f6/Menachem_1970.jpg/375px-Menachem_1970.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f6/Menachem_1970.jpg/500px-Menachem_1970.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"930\" data-file-height=\"1224\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Menachem_1970.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Menachem Banitt</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Menachem Banitt</b> (born <b>Max Berenblut</b>), born July 17, 1914, Antwerp, Belgium, died February 24, 2007, Israel,<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> was a Belgian\u2013Israeli scholar of medieval French culture and language and an internationally acclaimed expert on <a href=\"/wiki/Rashi\" title=\"Rashi\">Rashi</a>. Banitt was particularly known for his analysis of Rashi's occasional translation of words and phrases from <a href=\"/wiki/Hebrew\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hebrew\">Hebrew</a> or <a href=\"/wiki/Aramaic\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Aramaic\">Aramaic</a> into <a href=\"/wiki/Old_French\" title=\"Old French\">Old French</a>, written phonetically in Hebrew letters.\n</p><p>Banitt, who lived for most of his life in Israel, was a recipient of the <a href=\"/wiki/Israel_Prize\" title=\"Israel Prize\">Israel Prize</a> for the Study of Jewish Languages in 1999.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> He was also awarded the French honour of Officier of the <a href=\"/wiki/Ordre_des_Palmes_Acad%C3%A9miques\" title=\"Ordre des Palmes Acad\u00e9miques\">Ordre des Palmes Acad\u00e9miques</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Menachem_Banitt&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.obi-il.org/piks/lelien_1.pdf\">http://www.obi-il.org/piks/lelien_1.pdf</a><sup class=\"noprint Inline-Template\"><span style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">&#91;<i><a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Link_rot\" title=\"Wikipedia:Link rot\"><span title=\"&#160;Dead link since January 2018\">permanent dead link</span></a></i>&#93;</span></sup></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">(<cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20110921103840/http://cms.education.gov.il/EducationCMS/Units/PrasIsrael/TashnagTashsab/TASNAG_TASNAT_Rikuz.htm?DictionaryKey=Tashnat\">\"Archived copy\"</a>. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://cms.education.gov.il/EducationCMS/Units/PrasIsrael/TashnagTashsab/TASNAG_TASNAT_Rikuz.htm?DictionaryKey=Tashnat\">the original</a> on 2011-09-21<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2011-09-23</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp